criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  healthy females 18 through 40 years of age;

          -  have provided written informed consent after the nature of the study has been
             explained;

          -  are available for all visits scheduled for the study (i.e. are not planning to leave
             the area before the end of the study period);

          -  are in good health as determined by: medical history ,physical assessment

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  unwilling or unable to give written informed consent to participate in the study;

          -  pregnant (serum pregnancy test)

          -  unwilling to use acceptable birth control from screening and until at least 3 months
             after the final immunization

          -  nursing (breastfeeding) mothers
